! Hand-authored CHEMKIN mechanism for the end-to-end round-trip test
! (license-clean fixture, owned by the backend integration suite).
!
! Exercises the six kinetics forms whose CHEMKIN<->TCKDB fidelity the
! round trip guards: modified Arrhenius, Troe falloff + a collider list,
! PLOG, Chebyshev, simple third-body (bare +M), and a multi_arrhenius sum
! (a DUPLICATE pair). Plus NASA-7 thermo and transport for every species.
ELEMENTS
H O C AR
END

SPECIES
H  H2  O  O2  OH  H2O  CH3  CH4  AR
END

REACTIONS    CAL/MOLE   MOLES
! R1 -- modified Arrhenius, bimolecular, reversible
H + O2 <=> O + OH                        2.000E+14   0.000   16800.0
! R2 -- Troe falloff with a collider-efficiency list
CH3 + H (+M) <=> CH4 (+M)                1.270E+16  -0.630     383.0
    LOW  /  2.477E+33   -4.760   2440.0 /
    TROE /  0.7830   74.00   2941.0   6964.0 /
    H2/2.0/  H2O/6.0/  AR/0.70/
! R3 -- PLOG, bimolecular
OH + H2 <=> H + H2O                      2.160E+08   1.510    3430.0
    PLOG /  0.1    1.000E+08   1.400   3200.0 /
    PLOG /  1.0    2.160E+08   1.510   3430.0 /
    PLOG / 10.0    5.000E+08   1.600   3700.0 /
! R4 -- Chebyshev surface
H2 + O2 <=> OH + OH                      1.000E+00   0.000       0.0
    TCHEB /  300.0   2500.0 /
    PCHEB /  0.01    100.0 /
    CHEB  /  3   3 /
    CHEB  /  1.0E+01   2.0E-01   3.0E-02 /
    CHEB  /  4.0E-01   5.0E-02   6.0E-03 /
    CHEB  /  7.0E-02   8.0E-03   9.0E-04 /
! R5 -- simple third body (bare +M, no falloff): the [M] term raises the
! main-line concentration order by one, so O+O+M is order 3 -> cm6_mol2_s.
O + O + M <=> O2 + M                     1.000E+17   0.000       0.0
! R6 -- multi_arrhenius: a DUPLICATE pair summed into one k = Sigma_i A_i
! T^n_i exp(-Ea_i/RT). Each line is a modified-Arrhenius term; bimolecular
! (OH + OH) so every term keeps cm3_mol_s.
OH + OH <=> O + H2O                      3.570E+04   2.400   -2110.0
    DUP
OH + OH <=> O + H2O                      1.400E+13   0.000    5000.0
    DUP
END
